{"Name":"Update Detection","Description":"Deprecated. Update detection in Crowdstrike Falcon.","Script":"from SiemplifyAction import SiemplifyAction\nfrom SiemplifyUtils import output_handler\nfrom ScriptResult import EXECUTION_STATE_COMPLETED, EXECUTION_STATE_FAILED\n\nfrom TIPCommon.extraction import extract_configuration_param, extract_action_param\n\nfrom constants import (\n    INTEGRATION_NAME,\n    PRODUCT_NAME,\n    UPDATE_DETECTION_SCRIPT_NAME,\n    API_ROOT_DEFAULT,\n    DetectionStatusEnum,\n)\nfrom CrowdStrikeManager import CrowdStrikeManager\nfrom exceptions import CrowdStrikeParameterError\n\n\n@output_handler\ndef main():\n    siemplify = SiemplifyAction()\n    siemplify.script_name = UPDATE_DETECTION_SCRIPT_NAME\n\n    siemplify.LOGGER.info(\"----------------- Main - Param Init -----------------\")\n\n    api_root = extract_configuration_param(\n        siemplify,\n        provider_name=INTEGRATION_NAME,\n        param_name=\"API Root\",\n        default_value=API_ROOT_DEFAULT,\n    )\n    client_id = extract_configuration_param(\n        siemplify, provider_name=INTEGRATION_NAME, param_name=\"Client API ID\"\n    )\n    client_secret = extract_configuration_param(\n        siemplify, provider_name=INTEGRATION_NAME, param_name=\"Client API Secret\"\n    )\n    use_ssl = extract_configuration_param(\n        siemplify,\n        provider_name=INTEGRATION_NAME,\n        param_name=\"Verify SSL\",\n        input_type=bool,\n        is_mandatory=True,\n    )\n    customer_id = extract_configuration_param(\n        siemplify,\n        provider_name=INTEGRATION_NAME,\n        param_name=\"Customer ID\",\n        print_value=True,\n    )\n\n    detection_id = extract_action_param(\n        siemplify, param_name=\"Detection ID\", is_mandatory=True\n    )\n    status_to_update = extract_action_param(\n        siemplify, param_name=\"Status\", is_mandatory=True\n    )\n    assign_to = extract_action_param(siemplify, param_name=\"Assign Detection to\")\n\n    result_value = True\n    status = EXECUTION_STATE_COMPLETED\n\n    siemplify.LOGGER.info(\"----------------- Main - Started -----------------\")\n\n    try:\n        if status_to_update == DetectionStatusEnum.SELECT_ONE.value:\n            if not assign_to:\n                raise CrowdStrikeParameterError(\n                    'Either \"Status\" or \"Assign Detection To\" should have a proper value.'\n                )\n\n            status_to_update = None\n\n        manager = CrowdStrikeManager(\n            client_id=client_id,\n            client_secret=client_secret,\n            use_ssl=use_ssl,\n            api_root=api_root,\n            customer_id=customer_id,\n        )\n\n        uuid = manager.get_user_uuid_or_raise(assign_to) if assign_to else None\n\n        manager.update_detection(uuid, [detection_id], status_to_update)\n\n        output_message = (\n            f\"Successfully updated detection {detection_id} in {PRODUCT_NAME}.\"\n        )\n    except Exception as e:\n        output_message = (\n            f\"Error executing action '{UPDATE_DETECTION_SCRIPT_NAME}'. Reason: {e}\"\n        )\n        status = EXECUTION_STATE_FAILED\n        siemplify.LOGGER.error(output_message)\n        siemplify.LOGGER.exception(e)\n        result_value = False\n\n    siemplify.LOGGER.info(\"----------------- Main - Finished -----------------\")\n    siemplify.LOGGER.info(\n        f\"\\n  status: {status}\\n  is_success: {result_value}\\n  output_message: {output_message}\"\n    )\n    siemplify.end(output_message, result_value, status)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n","IntegrationIdentifier":"CrowdStrikeFalcon","ScriptResultName":"is_success","DynamicResultsMetadata":null,"Creator":"Admin","IsEnabled":true,"IsCustom":true,"AiGenerated":false,"IsSystem":false,"Version":1.0,"TimeoutSeconds":600,"IsAsync":null,"AsyncPollingIntervalInSeconds":300,"TotalIntervalTimeoutForAsyncInSeconds":3600,"Parameters":[{"CustomActionId":0,"IsMandatory":true,"DefaultValue":"","Description":"Specify the ID of the detection that needs to be updated.","Name":"Detection ID","Value":"","Type":0,"OptionalValues":null,"OptionalValuesJson":null},{"CustomActionId":0,"IsMandatory":true,"DefaultValue":"Select One","Description":"Specify the new status for the detection.","Name":"Status","Value":"","Type":15,"OptionalValues":["new","in_progress","true_positive","false_positive","ignored","closed","Select One"],"OptionalValuesJson":"[\"new\",\"in_progress\",\"true_positive\",\"false_positive\",\"ignored\",\"closed\",\"Select One\"]"},{"CustomActionId":0,"IsMandatory":false,"DefaultValue":"","Description":"Specify the email address of the Crowdstrike Falcon user, who needs to be assigned to this detection","Name":"Assign Detection to","Value":"","Type":0,"OptionalValues":null,"OptionalValuesJson":null}],"DefaultResultValue":"","PythonVersion":"None","ActionType":1,"SimulationData":{"Entities":null},"SimulationDataJson":null,"AICategories":[],"OutcomeCategories":[],"AIDescription":"### General Description\nUpdates the status and/or the assigned user of a specific detection in CrowdStrike Falcon. This action is primarily used for incident management and workflow orchestration, allowing analysts to programmatically transition detection states or reassign ownership within the CrowdStrike platform.\n\n### Parameters Description\n\n| Parameter | Type | Mandatory | Description |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Detection ID** | String | Yes | The unique identifier of the detection in CrowdStrike Falcon that needs to be updated. |\n| **Status** | Dropdown | Yes | The new status to assign to the detection (e.g., `new`, `in_progress`, `true_positive`, `false_positive`, `ignored`, `closed`). If set to `Select One`, the **Assign Detection to** parameter must be provided. |\n| **Assign Detection to** | String | No | The email address of the CrowdStrike Falcon user to whom the detection should be assigned. |\n\n### Additional Notes\n* **Validation Logic:** The action requires either a valid **Status** (anything other than `Select One`) or a value in **Assign Detection to**. If **Status** is `Select One` and no assignee is provided, the action will fail.\n* **User Resolution:** If an email is provided in **Assign Detection to**, the action performs an internal lookup to resolve that email to a CrowdStrike User UUID before performing the update.\n* **Deprecation:** Note that the metadata indicates this action is considered deprecated.\n\n### Flow Description\n1. **Initialization:** Retrieves integration configuration (API Root, Credentials, SSL settings) and action parameters.\n2. **Validation:** Checks if at least one update (Status or Assignee) is requested. If the status is `Select One` and no assignee is provided, it raises a parameter error.\n3. **User Lookup:** If an assignee email is provided, the action calls the CrowdStrike API to retrieve the corresponding User UUID.\n4. **Update Execution:** Sends a PATCH request to the CrowdStrike Falcon `detects/entities/detects/v2` endpoint with the specified Detection ID, the new status (if provided), and the User UUID (if provided).\n5. **Finalization:** Reports success if the API call completes without error, otherwise logs the failure reason.","AiShortDescription":null,"ParametersDescription":null,"EntityTypes":[]}